                      Instructions For Playing Xeno Quest

   Object  : The object of Xeno-Quest is to find your way out of Xeno's
             Dungeon, while killing everything in sight.  There are several
             levels with 100 rooms each that you will be wandering through
             on your quest to reach the Final Exit.  When a player reaches
             the Final Exit, that player will be added to the Hall Of Fame
             and the game will reset.

  Controls : Use of the arrow keys is required to move from place to place.
             The Number keys, 2 = Down, 8 = Up, 6 = Right, and 4 = Left, may
             be used instead or in additon to the extended arrow keys on your
             extended keyboard. (depends on the communication software that
             you use).  The 'F' Key is used to Fire your weapon and the 'U'
             Key is used to USE Potions.  Using the Number keys is faster
             than Using the Arrow Keys.  So when you find yourself up
             against one of Mean Monsters, you will need all the speed you
             can get.  If you are fast enough, you will find that dodging
             the incoming fire is a good way to stay alive longer.


  Firing Your Weapon :   Use the 'F' Key then type the direction which you
             want the projectile to go.  If your weapon is a Pea Shooter,
             it will most likely take several hits to destroy an opponent.
             You may fire several shots at a time.  Just keep pressing fire
             and the direction key and multiple shots will become air born.
             Be careful, because your shots can BOUNCE off of some items and
             could actually come back and hit you.


  Using Potions  :  Using Potions is just like firing your weapon, except
             that the projectile will do much more damage.  You can use
             potions to destroy Walls that have been built, including the
             ones you build.
                 Potions Look Like this ---> ญ
             A Player can carry up to 8 Potions.





  Building Walls : Wall Building is only allowed in rooms 51 through 99.
             Building walls is a good way to block others from getting to
             you and your items.  But, be careful you could block your self
             into a corner with no way out.. Built walls can be destroyed
             with potions.  When you build a wall, you are the owner of that
             wall.  A player can own up to 10 walls, Built or UnBuilt.
             Once you build one of your walls, it is there to stay until
             someone destroys it with a potion.  After it has been
             destroyed, you will allowed to re-build it at another location.
